# Release and PR workflow

- Never commit directly to `main`. Use `feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, or `release/` branches and open a PR.
- Every PR must update `CHANGELOG.md` under `[Unreleased]` (CI enforces this).
- Planned work belongs in `docs/ROADMAP.md`; release steps in `docs/RELEASE.md`.
- When implementing roadmap items, reference ROADMAP task numbers in the PR and check boxes when done.
- Before suggesting a release tag, ensure the current milestone in ROADMAP is complete, version bumped in `package.json`, and CHANGELOG section dated.
- Do not push to remote or create PRs unless the user explicitly asks.

## Git only — never `gh`

- **Do not run `gh`** (GitHub CLI) for any task: PRs, issues, checks, releases, or API queries.
- Use **git** for branch, commit, and push. Give the user a **compare URL** or ask them to open the PR in the GitHub UI.
- Example after push: `https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/compare/main...<branch>`
- Provide PR title and body in chat when helpful; the user creates the PR in the browser.
